\section{URL enumeration}{

The portal is a Vue SPA backed by a public REST API. The SPA reads the
backend host from \code{GET /rest/configuratie} (which exposes a \code{dmvbURL} field
pointing at \verb{https://dmvb.omgeving.vlaanderen.be/}) and then paginates
\verb{GET /api/v1/dossier?page=<n>&size=<k>} to enumerate the register. Page
size is capped server-side at 25; this handler walks every page until
\code{totalElements} is reached. The search index already carries \code{nummer},
\code{dossierType}, \code{titel}, and \code{initiatiefnemer}; the full record (locatie,
coordinator, domeinen, documenten) is one
\code{GET /api/v1/dossier/{nummer}} away.
}

\section{Geometry}{

Every detail record carries a \code{locatie} field in GeoJSON-style
(typically \code{MultiPolygon}) directly inline — no separate geometry call is
needed. Coordinates are in \strong{EPSG:31370} (Belgian Lambert 72), the
standard Flemish projection. When \code{write_sidecar = TRUE}, the geometry is
saved next to the sidecar as \verb{<document_id>.geometry.geojson}. The
sidecar carries \code{geometry_path} (absolute path to the .geojson) and
\code{geometry_crs} (\code{"EPSG:31370"}).

The GeoJSON is written with the GeoJSON-2008 \code{crs} member naming
\verb{urn:ogc:def:crs:EPSG::31370}; tools like QGIS / \code{sf::read_sf()} read
this fine, even though RFC 7946 deprecated the field. Coordinates are
kept in the source CRS — reproject downstream with \code{sf} if you need
WGS84.
}

\section{Attachments}{

Each \code{documenten[]} entry has a direct, public download URL
(\verb{https://dmvb.omgeving.vlaanderen.be/api/v1/dossier/\{nummer\}/document/\{uuid\}})
that requires no authentication. Documents are grouped by their portal
\code{type} (e.g. \emph{"Aanmelding"}, \emph{"Ontheffingsaanvraag"},
\emph{"Verslag toekenning ontheffing"}); the set is open-ended, so the handler
discovers whatever types a record has and emits one
\verb{attachment_urls_<slug>} / \verb{local_path_<slug>} list-column per discovered
type. The slug is the \code{type} string lowercased with non-alphanumerics
collapsed to underscores; \code{aanmelding}, \code{ontheffingsaanvraag}, and
\code{verslag_toekenning_ontheffing} are the common ones. \code{attachment_urls} /
\code{local_path} remain the deduplicated union (required by the schema).
}

\section{Filter coverage (v0.1)}{

\itemize{
\item \code{query} — case-insensitive substring match on \code{title} + \code{document_id}
(the \code{PR####} \code{nummer}). Client-side.
\item \code{niscode} — server-side NIS-code municipality filter (forwarded as the
API's \code{niscode} parameter). The list of municipalities + niscodes is
served at \verb{https://dmvb.omgeving.vlaanderen.be/api/v1/locatie}.
\item \code{nummer} — server-side exact / prefix match (forwarded as \code{nummer}).
\item \code{dossier_type} — client-side filter on \code{administratieveGegevens.dossierType}
(\code{"PROJECT_MER"} or \code{"VERZOEK_TOT_ONTHEFFING"}). The portal API ignores
